# Reflection

## What I Learned

Research synthesis involves integrating evidence from multiple sources rather than summarizing each source independently. Strong synthesis identifies common findings, explains disagreements, and presents balanced conclusions supported by the overall body of evidence.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

Include additional studies from different industries and countries to improve the diversity of evidence and determine whether findings remain consistent across different contexts.

